# Lore Engineering Standards

## Arrow Functions — Mandatory

All functions in `src/` MUST use arrow function syntax. `function` declarations are not allowed.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
export const buildApp = (deps: BuildAppDeps): FastifyInstance => { ... }
export const registerProject = async (db: DrizzleClient, input: Input): Promise<Output> => { ... }
const projectsController = (app: FastifyInstance, opts: Opts, done: DoneFn): void => { ... }
export default projectsController

// ❌ WRONG — never use these
export function buildApp(...) { ... }
export async function registerProject(...) { ... }
export default function projectsController(...) { ... }
```

## Layer Boundaries — Strict

The codebase uses a **Route → Controller → Service → Repository** four-layer architecture.

```
route → controller → service → repository
```

| Layer | Location | Responsibility | May Import | Must NOT Import |
|-------|----------|---------------|-----------|----------------|
| Route | `src/api/routes/` | Fastify plugin, URL, schema, preHandlers | Controllers | Services, Repositories, `drizzle-orm` |
| Controller | `src/api/controllers/` | Plain handler `(req, reply)`, response shaping | Services | Repositories, `drizzle-orm`, `pg` |
| Service | `src/services/` | Business logic, orchestration | Repositories | `fastify`, Fastify types |
| Repository | `src/repositories/` | Drizzle ORM queries only | `db/schema`, `db/client`, `drizzle-orm` | Services, Fastify |

```typescript
// ✅ Route — Fastify plugin wiring only
const projectsRoute = (app, opts, done) => {
  app.post('/register', { schema, preHandler: [requireAdminSecret] }, projectsController.register)
  done()
}

// ✅ Controller — plain handler, calls service
export const register = async (request, reply) => {
  const result = await projectsService.registerProject(request.body)
  reply.status(201)
  return result
}

// ✅ Service — business logic, calls repository
export const registerProject = async (input) => { ... }

// ✅ Repository — DB only
export const insertProject = async (db, data) => { /* drizzle query */ }

// ❌ WRONG — drizzle import in a route or controller
import { eq } from 'drizzle-orm'  // only allowed in repositories!

// ❌ WRONG — Fastify types in a service or repository
import { FastifyRequest } from 'fastify'  // only allowed in routes/controllers/middleware!
```

## File Naming

- Routes: `<resource>.route.ts` in `src/api/routes/`
- Controllers: `<resource>.controller.ts` in `src/api/controllers/` — export named handler functions
- Services: `<resource>.service.ts` in `src/services/`
- Repositories: `<resource>.repository.ts` in `src/repositories/`

## Tooling

- Package manager: **pnpm** only. Never run `npm install` or commit `package-lock.json`.
- Linter: `pnpm lint` (oxlint)
- Formatter: `pnpm format` (prettier)
- All new code must pass `pnpm lint` and `pnpm format:check` before commit.
